ENTRY            41790   20251222   20260518   20260518       4228
SUBENT        41790001   20251222   20260518   20260518       4228
BIB                 13         94
TITLE      Measurement of thermal neutron capture cross section
           and resonance integral of the 64Ni(n,gamma)65Ni
           reaction using an electron LINAC based neutron source
AUTHOR     (L.H.Khiem,N.A.Son,V.D.Cong,L.T.M.Nhat,P.T.Thanh,
           L.V.Huy,T.H.B.Phi,N.T.M.Sang,D.V.Trung,N.T.Binh,
           N.T.X.Thai,N.T.Dinh,H.S.Than,N.T.Vinh,V.N.Shvetsov,
           A.Yu.Dmitriev,V.V.Lobachev,S.B.Borzakov)
REFERENCE  (J,JRN,334,8261,2025)
           #doi:10.1007/s10967-025-10493-5
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB)
           Frank Laboratory of Neutron Physics.
           V.N.Shvetsov,A.Yu.Dmitriev,V.V.Lobachev,S.B.Borzakov,
           L.H.Khiem,V.D.Cong,L.T.M.Nhat,P.T.Thanh,N.T.X.Thai.
           Dzhelepov Laboratory of Nuclear Problems.
           L.H.Khiem,V.D.Cong,P.T.Thanh,T.H.B.Phi,N.T.X.Thai,
           (3VN IPH) L.H.Khiem, V.D.Cong,D.V.Trung,N.T.Binh,
           P.T.Thanh,T.H.B.Phi,N.T.X.Thai.
           (3VN NNR) N.T.Dinh,H.S.Than,N.T.Vinh.
           (3VN VN)  Dalat University, 01 Phu Dong Thien Vuong,
           Dalat, Lam Dong, Vietnam.
           L.T.M.Nhat,N.A.Son,N.T.M.Sang.
           (3VN VN) Institute of Fundamental and Applied Sciences,
           Duy Tan University, Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam.
           L.V.Huy.
FACILITY   (LINAC,4ZZZDUB) LUE-200 electron linear accelerator.
INC-SOURCE (BRST,PHOTO) Electron beam of 110 MeV energy, 50 Hz
           cycle repetition rate, 120 ns pulse width, average
           current ~ 10.8 muA.
           Tungsten-based alloy with a density of
           18.075 g cm.3, consisting of 90% W, 7% Ni, 3% Fe, was
           employed as the target (4 cm diameter, 10 cm length).
           Fast neutrons were thermalized by water inside
           Al container of 16 cm diameter, 25 cm height, filled
           with distilled water.
INC-SPECT  Thermal neutron flux at the sample position -
           6.480E+8 n/cm2/sec.
SAMPLE     Au sample size 10 x 10 x 0.05 mm, purity 99.98 %,
           weight - 0.09349 g ( bare), 0.09085  ( Cd-covered).
           Ni sample size 10 x 10 x 0.3 mm, purity 99.5 %,
           weight - 0.27488 g ( bare), 0.27943 ( Cd-covered).
           (28-NI-64,NAT=0.009256)
           (79-AU-197,NAT=1.00)
METHOD     (ACTIV) One set of Ni and Au samples was individually
           covered with 0.5 mm thick Cd foils, while other set of
           Ni and Au samples was uncovered. The samples were
           irradiated simultaneously and continuously for 54000 s.
           Cooling time :
           31.12 h ( uncovered Ni), 1.99 h (Cd-covered Ni),
           559.75 h ( uncovered Au), 559.81 h (Cd-covered Au).
           Shape factor of the epithermal neutron spectrum
           alpha = -0.180 +- 0.014 was experimentally determined
           using the cadmium-ratio dual monitor method.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) 8192 channel gamma spectrometer equipped with
           Canberra HPGe detector GC4018 of 59 mm diameter,
           61 mm height. Relative efficiency 40 % for 1332 keV
           gamma line, energy resolution 0.875 keV at 122 keV and
           1.8 keV at 1332 keV. Gamma detection efficiency was
           determined by a set of standard sources of 57Co, 60Co,
            109Cd, 133Ba, 134Cs, 152 Eu, 137Cs, 54Mn, 44Ti, 88Y.
           Genie2000 software was used for the acquisition and
           analysis of the gamma spectra.
ANALYSIS    Formulas (2) (reaction rate),(3) (cross section) ,
            (4,5) (resonance integral) from J,JRN,334,8261,2025
            were used in analysis.
            Cd cut-off energy was 0.55 eV.
            Data used in calculations:
           Gth/epi - thermal/epithermal neutron self-shielding
           coefficient
           F - cadmium correction factor
           Er - effective resonance energy
           G - geometrical correction factor
           g - Westcott correction factor
                      197Au                 64Ni
           Gth        0.987+-0.001          1.051+-0.001
           Gepi       0.453+-0.001          1.072+-0.002
           F          0.991                 1.0
           Er         5.65 eV               14,300 eV
           G          1.00814               1.005672
           g  (?)     1.0054                1.0002
            Coincidence summing correction factors:
                      Sample-detector distance 2.5 cm
           Gamma-ray energy (keV)
           366.27                  1.06
           1115.53                 1.03
           1481.84                 0.99
                      Sample-detector distance 5 cm
           Gamma-ray energy (keV)
           366.27                  1.03
           1115.53                 1.01
           1481.84                 1.0
CORRECTION  Neutron self-shielding, gamma self-absorption in the
           sample, coincidence summing, geometrical, and dead-time
           corrections.
HISTORY    (20251222C) M.M.
ENDBIB              94
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           97
